One note of clarification:

nfoscarini wrote:
&gt; You can make Heritrix run out of memory by using just 1 seed by
&gt; allowing it to hop endlessly around the internet.

This isn&#39;t true; in the default configurations, and other wise 
configurations, a crawl that&#39;s free to go &#39;anywhere&#39; may fill your disks 
or begin to run very, very slowly (as lookup structures become 
inefficiently large and disk-dependent) , but it should *not* run out of 
memory (RAM) triggering an OutOfMemoryExceptio n (OOME).

If it does, either there&#39;s a configuration issue or a bug.

- Gordon @ IA



      
